09 September - Apple Crisp

4 medium apples, peeled, cored and sliced (about 4 cups)
1/2 cup butter or margarine
1/2 cup flour
1 cup 40% bran flakes
3/4 cup packed brown sugar
1/2 teaspoon cinnamon

Arrange apple slices in shallow baking dish. Cream butter, blend in sugar, flour, and cinnamon. Stir in cereal. Sprinkle evenly over apples. Bake at 375F for 25-30 minutes. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream. 